<subSubSection id="C457FE5CC36722BF301904C8AE4FB3CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="526F084541373EE3BB9E08483D1ABEC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0148B16536B5F65E48F19953E95B94EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This is the only European genus of 
<taxonomicName id="2BB2FB32D1A744F2EC62169EB41D6699" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1910" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trichopolydesmidae</taxonomicName>
that is characterized by hook-shaped posterolateral cones on metaterga, see 
<bibRefCitation id="6A994FA34AF9969047BBFAB5369EFFD4" author="Ceuca, T" journalOrPublisher="Seria Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="91 - 97" refId="B16" refString="Ceuca, T, 1974. Noi contributii la cuonasterea diplopodelor din fauna Romaniei - New contributions to the knowledge of Diplopoda of the Roumanian Fauna. Studia Universitatis Babes-Bolyai. Seria Biologia 19: 91 - 97" title="Noi contributii la cuonasterea diplopodelor din fauna Romaniei - New contributions to the knowledge of Diplopoda of the Roumanian Fauna. Studia Universitatis Babes-Bolyai." volume="19" year="1974">Ceuca (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1A09AB63BAF3B0694AF9C95A9E87DAD3" author="Tabacaru, I" journalOrPublisher="Travaux de l'Institut de Speologie &quot; Emile Racovitza &quot;" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="71 - 82" refId="B57" refString="Tabacaru, I, 1975. Napocodesmus florentzae n. sp. Travaux de l'Institut de Speologie &quot;Emile Racovitza&quot; 14: 71 - 82" title="Napocodesmus florentzae n. sp." volume="14" year="1975">Tabacaru (1975)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
